docs.lead_paragraph: SOME books, and they are incomparably the finest ones, seem rather to have grown than to have been made. Such a book is "East of the Sun and West of the Moon," a new selection of twenty-one stories from the Norwegian folk tales collected many years ago by Peter Christen Asbjornsen and Jorgen Moe and translated into English by George Webbe Dasent.
